-- 
Hungary to Discuss 2012 Tax Changes Next Week, Nemzet Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-09-22T05:36:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/hungary-to-discuss-2012-tax-changes-next-week-nemzet-reports.html
The Hungarian government will
discuss changes to the 2012 tax system at a cabinet meeting on
Sept. 28,  Magyar Nemzet  reported, citing  Peter Szijjarto ,
spokesman for the prime minister.  The Economy Ministry proposed raising the monthly  minimum
wage  from 2012 by 18 percent to 92,000 ($424) forint and levying
an extra tax on incomes above 202,000 forint among other
changes, the newspaper said.  The extra levy may generate as much as 150 billion forint
in revenue, Magyar Nemzet reported, citing an executive at the
association of tax advisers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  